The article highlights the achievements of President Donald Trump during his first six months in office. It mentions that Trump has taken bold action to restore prosperity, keep Americans safe, and hold the government accountable. He has signed more than 40 bills and nearly 40 executive orders on various topics including healthcare, energy, and infrastructure. Trump has also focused on American energy, approving pipelines and rolling back environmental regulations. The article states that more than 800,000 new jobs have been created under Trump's administration. Vice President Mike Pence expresses his pride in serving alongside a president who prioritizes the armed forces and expresses confidence in making America safe, prosperous, and great again.